&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS:&lt;/strong&gt;  26 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASE&lt;/strong&gt;:  Meadows Health Centre &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONTRACT&lt;/strong&gt;: FIXED TERM – END 31st July 2021 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a part time Band 6 Mental Health Nurse Specialist to join Nottingham CityCare Community Homeless Health Service, working 26 hours a week fixed term until 31&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;st&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; July 2021 based at The Meadows Health Centre.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and energetic individual to join the Nottingham Community Homeless heath team.  The post is both interesting and varied and requires someone to show initiative and be a good team worker.  Applicants should have a responsible attitude and be able to demonstrate good communication skills. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be able to demonstrate effective communication, organisational and interpersonal skills, be able to work methodically under pressure, work autonomously providing high standard holistic health care needs to the vulnerable population of the City.  You will need to enjoy working as part of a multi-disciplinary team whilst having&lt;/span&gt; an understanding of the importance of confidentiality and a strong commitment to customer care. &lt;span&gt;Previous NHS experience is a distinct advantage. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Homeless Health team on 0115 883 1532 or Andrea Biddulph team manager on 07715050338&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
